cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CY 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing and machine translation. The use of morphological analyzers and interlinear glosses also suggests a focus on linguistic analysis and processing. 

It could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it involves the use of NMT and training on a dataset. 

cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible sub-category as the paper deals with the development of a translation system using AI techniques. 

cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is a possibility as the paper involves the use of NMT, which is a neural network-based approach. 

Finally, cs.CY (Computers and Society) is a less likely sub-category, but it could be argued that the paper has implications for the use of technology in promoting multilingualism and language preservation in low-resource settings.
